frus:attachment.p:
[353] *Q. What did he say?—A. He said
                                    that he sent people to Halifax, but not for military service;
                                    that he had a commission to do so.

Q. Did you not give that name under oath?—A. No, sir, I did not;
                                    I told the commissioner, and the grand jury, and you, my proper
                                    name, and the circumstances of it.
